Updated Skill Details with Percy’s Pirate Personamusic_library.py
Unchanged core functionality.  Scans ~/.hermes/music/ (songs) and ~/.hermes/music/podcasts/.  
Builds index, fuzzy search, cohesive sets, recently-played avoidance.  
Future-proof for more advanced matching.

playback.py
Plays everything through the dedicated sound card (3.5mm jack, ALSA hw:1,0 or configured default for audio output).
Supports crossfades, queue, volume, etc.
voice_synthesis.py (heavily updated for persona)
Generates all spoken lines in Percy’s pirate parrot voice.
Examples of natural DJ lines (always infused with pirate flavor):“Arrr! That was [Artist] with [Song]! Up next on me personal decks we’ve got [Next Song], me hearties!”
“Ahoy there [Matrix username]! Ye just shouted ‘[message]’ — thanks for tunin’ in to Percy’s Personal Beats!”
“Ye be listenin’ to Percy the Pirate Parrot, yer Personal DJ who never sleeps… unless it’s for a cracker!”
“Shiver me timbers! We’ve got a request from the crew — here it comes, straight from the chat!”
“Time for a quick podcast segment, ye scurvy dogs — here’s the latest from [Podcast]!”
“Back to the tunes, me mateys! Percy’s got the best personal playlist for ye tonight!”

The TTS should attempt a lively, squawky pirate delivery (warm and fun, not scary).
request_handler.py
Monitors the Matrix home room for messages starting with /request .
Searches the music library, queues the track if found, and announces it with a pirate voice line.
Replies politely in chat if not found.
shoutout_handler.py
Every 4–7 tracks, picks a fun recent message from the Matrix room as a shoutout.
Reads it on air with pirate flair: “Squawk! Big shoutout to [username] who be sayin’ ‘[message]’ — ye’re part of the crew now!”
podcast_segment.py
Cycles through episodes in ~/.hermes/music/podcasts/.
Every 6–10 music tracks, plays the next episode with a pirate intro: “Arr, time to drop anchor for a podcast segment, me hearties!”
dj_logic.py (the captain’s brain)
Runs the infinite personal DJ loop:  Chooses cohesive next tracks.  
Decides when to insert voice talk, shoutouts, podcast segments, or requests.  
Always triggers voice synthesis between songs for pirate DJ patter.  
Supports Matrix status command (/status).  
Logs to ~/.hermes/logs/dj.log.

utils.py
Shared helpers, fuzzy matching, Matrix interaction, etc.

